## VLESS+Reality Clients

VLESS+Reality makes your VPN traffic indistinguishable from legitimate TLS 1.3
connections to **{{ reality_sni }}**. The following client applications support
VLESS+Reality:

### Supported Client Apps

| Platform | App | Notes |
|----------|-----|-------|
| **Android** | [v2rayNG](https://github.com/2dust/v2rayNG) | Recommended for Android; supports VLESS+Reality natively |
| **Windows** | [v2rayN](https://github.com/2dust/v2rayN) | Full-featured Windows client with GUI |
| **Linux / macOS** | [Nekoray](https://github.com/MatsuriDayo/nekoray) | Cross-platform client with Xray/sing-box core |
| **iOS / macOS** | [Shadowrocket](https://apps.apple.com/app/shadowrocket/id932747118) | Paid app; supports VLESS+Reality on iOS |

### Importing via VLESS Share Link

1. Open the 3x-ui web panel at `https://{{ domain }}{{ xui_path_prefix }}/`
2. Navigate to the inbound settings and create a new client (or use the
   pre-configured initial client)
3. Copy the **VLESS share link** (starts with `vless://...`)
4. In your client app:
   - **v2rayNG:** Tap the `+` button → "Import config from clipboard"
   - **v2rayN:** Click "Servers" → "Import from clipboard"
   - **Nekoray:** Click "Program" → "Add profile from clipboard"
   - **Shadowrocket:** The link is auto-detected from clipboard on app open

### Importing via QR Code

1. In the 3x-ui panel, click the QR code icon next to the client entry
2. Scan the QR code with your client app:
   - **v2rayNG:** Tap `+` → "Import config from QR code"
   - **Shadowrocket:** Use the built-in QR scanner

### Expected Connection Behavior

- The connection appears as a normal TLS 1.3 handshake to `{{ reality_sni }}`
- DPI systems see traffic that is indistinguishable from HTTPS browsing
- Initial connection may take 1-2 seconds longer than standard VPN due to the
  Reality handshake
- If the connection fails, verify that `{{ reality_sni }}` supports TLS 1.3
  from your network

