## AmneziaWG Clients

AmneziaWG provides WireGuard-based VPN with DPI-resistant obfuscation. The
server listens on **{{ awg_listen_port or "configured port" }}/udp**.

### Supported Client Apps

| Platform | App | Notes |
|----------|-----|-------|
| **Android / iOS** | [AmneziaVPN](https://amnezia.org/) | Official Amnezia client; supports all 2.0 parameters |
| **Windows / macOS / Linux** | [AmneziaVPN Desktop](https://amnezia.org/) | Official desktop client with full 2.0 support |
| **All platforms** | Official WireGuard clients | Basic support; may not support 2.0 obfuscation parameters (S3/S4, H1-H4) |

> **Important:** To use the full AmneziaWG 2.0 obfuscation parameter set
> (S3, S4, H1-H4, I1-I5), you **must** use an AmneziaVPN client. Standard
> WireGuard clients do not support these parameters.

### Importing .conf File

1. Open the AmneziaWG panel at `https://{{ domain }}{{ awg_panel_path_prefix }}/`
2. Create a new peer or use the pre-configured initial peer
3. Download the `.conf` configuration file
4. Import into your client:
   - **AmneziaVPN (mobile):** Tap "Add connection" → "Import from file" → select the `.conf` file
   - **AmneziaVPN (desktop):** Click "Import" → select the `.conf` file
   - **Official WireGuard client:** "Add Tunnel" → "Import tunnel(s) from file"

### AmneziaWG 2.0 Parameter Compatibility

{% if awg_obfuscation %}
This server is configured with AmneziaWG 2.0 obfuscation parameters. The
S and H parameters **must match exactly** between server and client:

| Parameter | Value | Description |
|-----------|-------|-------------|
| S1 | {{ awg_obfuscation.s1 }} | Init packet magic header |
| S2 | {{ awg_obfuscation.s2 }} | Response packet magic header |
| S3 | {{ awg_obfuscation.s3 }} | Init packet junk size (2.0) |
| S4 | {{ awg_obfuscation.s4 }} | Response packet junk size (2.0) |
| H1 | {{ awg_obfuscation.h1 }} | Header transform param 1 |
| H2 | {{ awg_obfuscation.h2 }} | Header transform param 2 |
| H3 | {{ awg_obfuscation.h3 }} | Header transform param 3 |
| H4 | {{ awg_obfuscation.h4 }} | Header transform param 4 |
| Jc | {{ awg_obfuscation.jc }} | Junk packet count |
| Jmin | {{ awg_obfuscation.jmin }} | Min junk packet size |
| Jmax | {{ awg_obfuscation.jmax }} | Max junk packet size |

These parameters are automatically included in the `.conf` file downloaded
from the AmneziaWG panel.
{% else %}
Obfuscation parameters were auto-generated during deployment. They are
included in the `.conf` files downloaded from the AmneziaWG panel.
{% endif %}

> **Note:** If a client cannot connect, verify that the client app version
> supports AmneziaWG 2.0. Older versions may not recognize the S3/S4 and
> H-range parameters.

