## Tailscale Setup

Tailscale provides a mesh overlay network for secure management and
inter-node connectivity.

### Joining the Tailnet

{% if tailscale_auth_key %}
This deployment was configured with a Tailscale auth key. The Tailscale
container should have automatically joined the tailnet during deployment.

**To verify:**
```bash
docker compose exec tailscale tailscale status
```
{% else %}
This deployment requires manual Tailscale authentication:

1. Check the Tailscale container logs for the authentication URL:
   ```bash
   docker compose logs tailscale | grep "https://login.tailscale.com"
   ```

2. Open the URL in your browser and authenticate with your Tailscale account

3. Verify the device has joined:
   ```bash
   docker compose exec tailscale tailscale status
   ```
{% endif %}

### Device Authorization

After the VM joins the tailnet:

1. Go to the [Tailscale admin console](https://login.tailscale.com/admin/machines)
2. Find the new device and approve it if your tailnet requires authorization
3. Optionally, configure the device as an **exit node** to route all client
   traffic through the VPN server:
   ```bash
   docker compose exec tailscale tailscale up --advertise-exit-node
   ```
4. In the admin console, approve the exit node route

### Using Tailscale on Client Devices

1. Install the Tailscale client on your device:
   - **Windows / macOS / Linux:** [tailscale.com/download](https://tailscale.com/download)
   - **Android / iOS:** Available in app stores

2. Sign in with the same Tailscale account used for the VPN server

3. Your device will automatically discover the VPN server on the tailnet

4. To use the server as an exit node (route all traffic through it):
   - **Desktop:** Click the Tailscale tray icon → "Exit Node" → select the server
   - **Mobile:** Open Tailscale → tap "Exit Node" → select the server
